ge High School to discuss his illegal advances toward a 16-year-old girl, 41-year-old assistant principal Roosevelt Holloman pulled out a gun and shot principal Raymond Screws, 51, to death. Holloman also shot at two other school officials but missed. Holloman surrendered his gun to a janitor and waited until being arrested. He was later convicted of [[first-degree murder]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=888&dat=19771213&id=N-8LAAAAIBAJ&sjid=HVoDAAAAIBAJ&pg=3129,4205065 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120723175746/http://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=888&dat=19771213&id=N-8LAAAAIBAJ&sjid=HVoDAAAAIBAJ&pg=3129,4205065 |url-status=dead |archive-date=2012-07-23 |title=Principle (sic) shot to death |publisher=News.google.com |date=1977-12-13 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1346&dat=19771213&id=ZnUsAAAAIBAJ&sjid=o_oDAAAAIBAJ&pg=6331,2860961 |title=School Principle (sic) Shot to Death |publisher=News.google.com |date=1977-12-13 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=5gMMAAAAIBAJ&sjid=g1oDAAAAIBAJ&pg=3946,830644&dq=principal+shot+screws+kissed&hl=en |title=Slayer of school principal convicted of first-degree murder |publisher=News.google.ca |date=1978-06-10 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 4, 1978\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n| Everton Lazarus, 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Michael Kittrell, 15, was stabbed to death by another student at John Adams High School.<ref>{{cite news|author=[ Displaying Abstract ] |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1978/02/03/archives/youth-is-arrested-in-students-killing.html |title=Youth Is Arrested In Student's Killing |publisher=Select.nytimes.com |date=2011-03-02 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 22, 1978\n| [[Lansing, Michigan]], United States\n| Roger Needham, 15\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| Roger Needham, a 15-year-old student, shot two students at Everett High School. One of the students, 15-year-old Bill Draher, died of his gunshot wound.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kresnak |first=Jack |url=http://www.justicejournalism.org/crimeguide/chapter02/chapter02_pg02.html |title=Juvenile Justice |publisher=Justicejournalism.org |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 18, 1978\n| [[Austin, Texas]], United States\n| John Daniel Christian, 13\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 13-year-old honor student John Christian, son of former LBJ press secretary [[George Christian (journalist)|George Christian]], fatally shot his teacher, 29-year-old Rod Grayson, three times at Murchison Junior High School. Christian fled the school building and was subdued by gym coach Larry Schirpik. Christian's attorney, Roy Minton, argued Christian was [[Insanity defence|not guilty by reason of insanity]], and district attorney Ronnie Earle did not object. The case did not go to trial. Christian was treated for two years at a private mental health facility in Dallas paid for by his family.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.michaelcorcoran.net/archives/1469 |title=Austin\u2019s Secret: Killing in the Classroom 1978 |publisher=MichaelCorcoran.net |accessdate=2012-12-17}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 1978\n| [[Winnipeg, Manitoba]], Canada\n| Vaughan Pollen, 17\n| 1 dead\n|\n| A 16-year-old student, Kenneth Maitland, was shot to death with a shotgun by 17-year-old student, Vaughan Pollen, at Sturgeon Creek Regional Secondary School. Pollen was charged with murder but during the trial found unfit to stand trial by reason of a mental disorder. He was committed to a mental health facility for treatment of [[paranoid schizophrenia]] and treated for 7 years.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/background/school-shootings/ |title=Attacks on students and staff |publisher=Cbc.ca |date=2008-09-23 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100130091329/http://www.cbc.ca/news/background/school-shootings/ |archivedate=January 30, 2010 }}</ref>\n|-\n| January 29, 1979\n| [[San Diego, California]], United States\n| Brenda Spencer\n| 2 dead\n| 9 injured\n| A 16-year-old student, Brenda Spencer, began shooting from her home at children who were waiting outside Cleveland Elementary School for principal Burton Wragg (aged 53) to open the gates. She injured eight children. Wragg was killed while trying to help the children. Custodian Mike Suchar (aged 56) was killed while trying to pull a student to safety. Asked by a reporter why she committed the crime, Spencer is said to have replied \"[[I Don't Like Mondays]]\"\n|}\n\n===1980s===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:65px;\"| Date\n! style=\"width:85px;\"| Location\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Attacker(s)\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" style=\"width:75px;\"| Dead{{r|group=lower-alpha|note_a}}\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" style=\"width:75px;\"| Injured{{r|group=lower-alpha|note_a}}\n! Description\n|-\n| January 7, 1980\n| [[Stamps, Arkansas]], United States\n| Evan Hampton, 16\n| 1 dead\n| \n| Evan Hampton, 16, high school freshman student at Stamps High School, shot Mike Sanders, 19, twice in the chest and once in the temple, killing him instantly. He was arrested.<ref>{{cite news|url= https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=799&dat=19800109&id=0CccAAAAIBAJ&sjid=41cEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6542,692754|newspaper=The Bryan Times|title=Death of student makes no sense|date=January 9, 1980}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 31, 1980\n| [[Hueytown, Alabama]], United States\n| Rudy Farmer, 17\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| 17-year-old Rudy Farmer pulled out a pistol and shot a fellow student in the art room at Hueytown High School.  That student was wounded.  Farmer fatally shot himself.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1454&dat=19801101&id=CcgsAAAAIBAJ&sjid=RRMEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6542,12997|newspaper=The Star-News|title=Student killed in school shooting|date=November 1, 1980}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 2, 1981\n| [[Greenville, South Carolina]], United States\n| Jewel Loraine Garrett, 18\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Henry Chiariello, a 30-year-old social studies teacher, was stabbed to death at Greenville High School by 18-year-old student Jewel Garrett. Garrett was later sentenced to life in prison.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=KnQQAAAAIBAJ&sjid=m4sDAAAAIBAJ&pg=5899,421593&dq=henry+chiariello |title=Slain |publisher=News.google.com |date=1981-10-03 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 12, 1982\n| [[Miami, Florida]], United States\n| Steven Wayne Holmes, 15\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Francisco Walker, 24, a sixth-grade teacher at Edison Middle School, was stabbed to death by a teenaged trespasser, 15-year-old Steven Wayne Holmes. He was later arrested and charged with first degree murder.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=kNMRAAAAIBAJ&sjid=h-4DAAAAIBAJ&pg=6038,4608633&dq=school+stabbing+death&hl=en |title=Teacher stabbed to death |publisher=News.google.ca |date=1982-01-13 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=WOgTAAAAIBAJ&sjid=EwYEAAAAIBAJ&pg=5606,5408156&dq=francisco+walker&hl=en |title=15-Year-Old Arrested In Slaying Of Teacher |publisher=News.google.ca |date=1982-01-13 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 19, 1982\n| [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]], United States\n| Pat Lizotte, 17\n| 1 dead\n| 3 injured\n| Clarence Piggott, a 55-year-old psychology and sociology teacher, was shot to death, and two students were wounded by a high school senior. The student was later shot and wounded by police before arrest.<ref>{{cite news|author=AP |url=https://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F30911FB3D5D0C738EDDAA0894DA484D81 |title=The New York Times Article March 20, 1982 |location=Las Vegas (Nev) |publisher=Select.nytimes.com |date=1982-03-20 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=FLQSAAAAIBAJ&sjid=YvkDAAAAIBAJ&pg=6010,1797067&dq= Shooting spree], ''[[Spokane Chronicle]]'' (March 22, 1982)</ref> Lizotte is sentenced to two consecutive life sentences without the possibility of parole. However, he was granted parole on March 6, 2017 after a Nevada law banning life without parole for juveniles reduced his sentence to 20 years to life.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news3lv.com/news/local/student-convicted-in-1982-shooting-death-of-valley-hs-teacher-granted-parole|title=Student convicted in 1982 shooting death of Valley HS teacher granted parole|last=Garcia|first=John Treanor and Tony|work=KSNV|access-date=2017-07-06|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|-\n| April 7, 1982\n| [[Littleton, Colorado]], United States\n| [[1982 Deer Creek Shooting|Jason Rocha]], 14\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Jason Rocha, a 14-year-old student, shot and killed 13 year-old Scott Darwin Michael, a fellow student at [[Deer Creek Middle School]] in Littleton, Colorado. Rocha was charged as an adult and sentenced to 12-years in prison for the murder.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1876&dat=19840304&id=U0IsAAAAIBAJ&sjid=rM4EAAAAIBAJ&pg=5024,759361 |title=These Kids Are \u2018Middle-Class Murderers |publisher=News.google.com |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 20, 1983\n| [[St. Louis County, Missouri]], United States\n| David F. Lawler, 14\n| 2 dead\n| 1 injured\n| 14-year-old David F. Lawler took two family pistols to school and shot two classmates, killing one and injuring the other. In a murders/suicide note he had brought with him, he outlined his intention to kill the next person heard speaking ill of his older brother Ken. He entered a study hall classroom and opened fire, hitting the two victims. The first was fatally shot in the stomach, and the second received a non-fatal gunshot wound to the abdomen. After, he said, \"no one will ever call my brother a pussy again\". He then committed suicide. See [[Parkway South Junior High School shooting|Parkway South Junior High School killings]] for more information.\n|-\n| May 16, 1983\n| [[Dallas, Texas]], United States\n| Billy Conn Gardner\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Billy Conn Gardner, a friend of a food service worker's husband, robbed the [[Lake Highlands High School]] cafeteria at gunpoint, shot the food service director, and left with $1,600. The food service director, Thelma Row, died eleven days later from the injuries. Gardner was later apprehended, convicted, and sentenced to death via Lethal Ejection for the crime. The State of Texas executed him on February 16, 1995.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://lakehighlands.advocatemag.com/2014/03/history-shooting-lake-highlands-cafeteria-worker-remembered/|author=Toler, Carol|title=History: Shooting of Lake Highlands cafeteria worker remembered|date=2014-03-04|accessdate=2018-04-26|publisher=Advocate Magazine (Lake Highlands)}}</ref>\n|-\n| June 3, 1983\n| [[Eppstein|Eppstein-Vockenhausen]], Germany\n| Karel Charva, 34\n| 6 dead\n| 14 injured\n| [[Eppstein school shooting]]. Thirty-five-year-old [[Czechs|Czech]] [[refugee]] Karel Charva, fatally shot three students, a teacher and a police officer, and injured another 14 people with two [[semi-automatic pistol]]s, before committing [[suicide]] at the [[Heinrich Friedrich Karl vom und zum Stein|Freiherr-vom-Stein]] [[Gesamtschule]].<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1983/06/04/world/around-the-world-classroom-gun-rampage-leaves-6-germans-dead.html Classroom Gun Rampage Leaves 6 Germans Dead], ''[[The New York Times]]'' (June 4, 1983)</ref>\n|-\n| December 16, 1983\n| [[Rockford, Illinois]], United States\n| Michael Graham, 15\n|\n| 1 injured\n| Michael Graham, a 15-year-old student at Boylan Central Catholic High School, shot and wounded his German teacher, Sharon Mundt, who had disciplined him for misbehavior.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=uSEVAAAAIBAJ&sjid=UwYEAAAAIBAJ&pg=3636,1012288&dq= Student's threat to shoot teacher was dismissed by classmates as joke], ''[[Ocala Star-Banner]]'' (December 18, 1983)</ref>\n|-\n| March 13, 1984\n| [[Castres]], France\n| \n| 2 dead\n|\n| A 15-year-old student killed his teacher, who had sent him to the headmaster for being late, and shot himself in the head. He died on the way to the hospital.<ref>[http://suche.abendblatt.de:8000/article.php?xmlurl=http://87.230.59.37/ha/1984/xml/19840314xml/habxml840103_9060.xml&pdfurl=http://87.230.59.37/ha/1984/pdf/19840314.pdf/ASV_HAB_19840314_HA_032.pdf Lehrer erschossen]{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, ''[[Hamburger Abendblatt]]'' (March 14, 1984)</ref>\n|-\n|March 29, 1985\n|[[Spartanburg, South Carolina|Spartanburg]], [[South Carolina]], United States\n|\n|\n|\n|A 15 year old freshman held four students [[hostage]] at [[Paul M. Dorman High School]], after leaving school grounds when being accused of drinking, and returning to the school with a loaded .38 Colt [[revolver]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.goupstate.com/news/19990502/student-gunman-took-hostages-in-spartanburg-14-years-ago-it-happened-here|title=Student gunman took hostages in Spartanburg 14 years ago It happened here|last=PREVATTE|first=PAM|work=GoUpstate|access-date=2018-02-20|language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n|September 4, 1985\n|[[Richmond, Virginia]], United States\n| Student, 12-years-old\n| 1 dead\n|\n| At the end of the second day of school at East End Middle School, a 12-year-old boy shot a girl with his mother's gun. <ref> https://www.k12academics.com/school-shootings/history-school-shootings-united-states}</ref>\n|-\n| October 18, 1985\n| [[Detroit]], [[Michigan]], United States\n| \n| \n| 6 injured\n| During halftime of the homecoming football game between [[Northwestern High School (Michigan)|Northwestern]] and [[Murray-Wright High School|Murray-Wright]], a boy who had been in a fight earlier that day retaliated with a shotgun, wounding six students.<ref>{{cite news |newspaper=[[Houston Chronicle]] |title=6 Shot, Injured at Homecoming|url=https://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl/1985_45387/6-shot-injured-at-homecoming.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |newspaper=Houston Chroni