ren Lloyd Fowler, 16\n| \n| 4 injured\n| Three months after he was expelled, Darren Lloyd Fletcher returned to his former school, Higham Ferrers School, shooting a deputy head in the head, and injuring a teacher and two 12-year old pupils with glass and shrapnel, before he was overpowered by staff. He was out to kill his rival for the affections of a 16-year-old girl who was a student at the school.<ref>{{cite news |newspaper= The Glasgow Herald | title = Boy Rambo gets life | url = https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2507&dat=19880625&id=8jNAAAAAIBAJ&sjid=T1kMAAAAIBAJ&pg=3452,6976776&hl=en | date = June 25, 1988 | accessdate = December 29, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 11, 1988\n| [[Pinellas Park, Florida]], United States\n| Jason Edward Harless, 15 <br> Jason McCoy, 15\n| 1 dead\n| 3 injured\n| [[Pinellas Park High School#School shooting|Pinellas Park High School shooting]]. Jason Harless and Jason McCoy, both students, brought stolen guns to school, where they killed principal Richard Allen , and injured an assistant principal and an assistant physical education teacher. Harless was shot and wounded by police, and McCoy was arrested without injury. Both served prison terms.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=pMUMAAAAIBAJ&sjid=J2EDAAAAIBAJ&pg=6178,5476026&dq= Student was treated at mental hospital], ''[[St. Petersburg Times]]'' (February 13, 1988)</ref>\n|-\n| November 22, 1988\n| [[Abilene, Texas]], United States\n| Mason Staggs, 16\n| \n| 1 injured\n| Mason Staggs, 16, shot Cooper High School teacher Rick Maloney in the face with a derringer, severely injuring him. Staggs then left the school and went fishing.<ref>{{cite news |newspaper=[[Abilene Reporter-News]] |url=http://www.texnews.com/local97/staggs021497.html |title=Mason Staggs denied double jeopardy claim |date=February 14, 1997 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050320190338/http://www.texnews.com/local97/staggs021497.html |archivedate=March 20, 2005 }}</ref>\n|-\n| December 16, 1988\n| [[Virginia Beach, Virginia]], United States\n| Nicholas Elliott, 16\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| Nicholas Elliott came to Atlantic Shores Christian School with a firearm bought by an adult relative. He shot two teachers, one fatally, before entering a portable classroom full of students. The gun jammed and Elliott was tackled. Questioned after the shooting, Elliott complained of being teased and bullied. He was later sentenced to life in prison in 1989.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lorrainewakeland.com/pdfarchive/jammed_gun.pdf |title=Jammed gun holds toll to 1 dead; student held |format=PDF |accessdate=2011-03-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110713232358/http://www.lorrainewakeland.com/pdfarchive/jammed_gun.pdf |archive-date=2011-07-13 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5oabRaJVmysC&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_summary_r&cad=0 |title=Leonard Beeghley Homicide:A Sociological Explanation |publisher=Books.google.com |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 24, 1989\n| [[Rauma, Finland|Rauma]], Finland\n| Tero Toivola, 14\n| 2 dead\n|\n| [[Raumanmeri school shooting]]. Two students, 15-year-old Kristian Johtela and 14-year-old Juha Suominen, were fatally shot by 14-year-old student Tero Toivola at the Raumanmeri [[Secondary School]], in [[Rauma, Finland]]. The shooter claimed to be a victim of bullying.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.yle.fi/news/left/id74423.html|title=School Shootings Rare in Finland|publisher=[[YLE]]|date=2007-11-07|accessdate=2007-11-07}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n===1990s===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:65px;\"| Date\n! style=\"width:85px;\"| Location\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Attacker(s)\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" style=\"width:75px;\"| Dead{{r|group=lower-alpha|note_a}}\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" style=\"width:75px;\"| Injured{{r|group=lower-alpha|note_a}}\n! Description\n|-\n| May 20, 1990\n| [[Centerville, Tennessee]], United States\n| Donald Wayne Givens, 50\n| 1 dead\n| \n| Hickman County High School Principal Ron Wallace, 41, was shot and killed by Science teacher Donald Wayne Givens, 50, when Givens was caught by Wallace attempting to set fire to several areas of the high school two days before graduation ceremonies were scheduled.<ref>{{cite news|title=School hit by slaying and blaze Principal shot; teacher held|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1310&dat=19900521&id=wcJWAAAAIBAJ&sjid=0eoDAAAAIBAJ&pg=6655,5338612|newspaper=The Register-Guard|date=May 21, 1990}}</ref>\n|-\n| August 26, 1990\n| [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]], United States\n| Curtis Collins, 15\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Curtis Collins, a sophomore at Eldorado High School, shot and killed 16-year-old Donnie Lee Bolden inside the school cafeteria. Police said that the shooting was gang-related.<ref>{{cite web|author=Benjamin Grove |url=http://www.lasvegassun.com/news/1998/jun/20/memories-linger-for-victims-mother/ |title=Memories linger for victim\u2019s mother |publisher=Lasvegassun.com |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 21, 1990\n| [[Houston, Texas]], United States\n| ..., 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| A 16-year-old girl fatally stabbed her classmate, 18-year-old Anthony Johnson, in the upper back with a [[hunting knife]] in a classroom at [[Jesse H. Jones High School]], in [[Houston]], [[Texas]]; Johnson later died at [[Ben Taub Hospital]]. The suspect was then placed in the Harris County Juvenile Probation Department. It was reported that the possible motive was the victim making an insulting comment about the suspect's clothing.<ref>Markley, Melanie. \"[https://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl?id=1996_1371129 Studying our Schools: Challenges / Safety matters: Issue is No. 1 concern with parents].\" ''[[Houston Chronicle]]''. October 13, 1996.</ref><ref>Hanson, Eric. \"[https://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl?id=1990_731137 Teen fatally stabbed in classroom / Victim pays for insult t