en for medical attention. The couple had been married for some 15 years and had two boys. Taylor-Israel is said to have gone to the school to pick up her son when the shooting occurred. Eyewitnesses claim that Israel left the scene in a motor vehicle following the shooting. He was later apprehended by police. A firearm was retrieved some two days later by police. Taylor-Israel was said to have made three reports to the Questelles Police Station in relation to death threats, days before her death. <ref>{{Cite web|url= https://www.iwnsvg.com/2020/01/30/cuba-born-nurse-shot-killed-at-school-in-st-vincent/ |title= Cuba-born nurse shot, killed at school in St. Vincent |date=31 January 2020|website=iWitness News}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://searchlight.vc/searchlight/front-page/2020/02/04/gun-retrieved-in-connection-with-death-of-cuban-born-nurse/ |title= Gun retrieved in connection with death of Cuban-born nurse |date=4 February 2020|website=Searchlight News}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[School bullying]]\n*[[School shooting]]\n*[[List of school-related attacks]]\n*[[List of school shootings in the United States]]\n*[[List of attacks related to primary schools]]\n*[[List of attacks related to post-secondary schools]]\n*[[List of rampage killers: School massacres]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist|refs=\n<ref name=note_a>Including death or injury of attacker(s), when applicable.</ref>}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181140/http://www.schoolsecurity.org/trends/school_violence00-01.html School-Related Deaths, School Shootings, & School Violence Incidents: 2000\u20132001], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181216/http://www.schoolsecurity.org/trends/school_violence02-03.html School-Related Deaths, School Shootings, & School Violence Incidents: 2002\u20132003], ''National School Safety and Security Services''\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110722181239/ht