on Rocha]], 14\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Jason Rocha, a 14-year-old student, shot and killed 13 year-old Scott Darwin Michael, a fellow student at [[Deer Creek Middle School]] in Littleton, Colorado. Rocha was charged as an adult and sentenced to 12-years in prison for the murder.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1876&dat=19840304&id=U0IsAAAAIBAJ&sjid=rM4EAAAAIBAJ&pg=5024,759361 |title=These Kids Are \u2018Middle-Class Murderers |publisher=News.google.com |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 20, 1983\n| [[St. Louis County, Missouri]], United States\n| David F. Lawler, 14\n| 2 dead\n| 1 injured\n| 14-year-old David F. Lawler took two family pistols to school and shot two classmates, killing one and injuring the other. In a murders/suicide note he had brought with him, he outlined his intention to kill the next person heard speaking ill of his older brother Ken. He entered a study hall classroom and opened fire, hitting the two victims. The first was fatally shot in the stomach, and the second received a non-fatal gunshot wound to the abdomen. After, he said, \"no one will ever call my brother a pussy again\". He then committed suicide. See [[Parkway South Junior High School shooting|Parkway South Junior High School killings]] for more information.\n|-\n| May 16, 1983\n| [[Dallas, Texas]], United States\n| Billy Conn Gardner\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Billy Conn Gardner, a friend of a food service worker's husband, robbed the [[Lake Highlands High School]] cafeteria at gunpoint, shot the food service director, and left with $1,600. The food service director, Thelma Row, died eleven days later from the injuries. Gardner was later apprehended, convicted, and sentenced to death via Lethal Ejection for the crime. The State of Texas executed him on February 16, 1995.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://lakehighlands.advocatemag.com/2014/03/history-shooting-lake-highlands-cafeteria-worker-remembered/|author=Toler, Carol|title=History: Shooting of Lake Highlands cafeteria worker remembered|date=2014-03-04|accessdate=2018-04-26|publisher=Advocate Magazine (Lake Highlands)}}</ref>\n|-\n| June 3, 1983\n| [[Eppstein|Eppstein-Vockenhausen]], Germany\n| Karel Charva, 34\n| 6 dead\n| 14 injured\n| [[Eppstein school shooting]]. Thirty-five-year-old [[Czechs|Czech]] [[refugee]] Karel Charva, fatally shot three students, a teacher and a police officer, and injured another 14 people with two [[semi-automatic pistol]]s, before committing [[suicide]] at the [[Heinrich Friedrich Karl vom und zum Stein|Freiherr-vom-Stein]] [[Gesamtschule]].<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1983/06/04/world/around-the-world-classroom-gun-rampage-leaves-6-germans-dead.html Classroom Gun Rampage Leaves 6 Germans Dead], ''[[The New York Times]]'' (June 4, 1983)</ref>\n|-\n| December 16, 1983\n| [[Rockford, Illinois]], United States\n| Michael Graham, 15\n|\n| 1 injured\n| Michael Graham, a 15-year-old student at Boylan Central Catholic High School, shot and wounded his German teacher, Sharon Mundt, who had disciplined him for misbehavior.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=uSEVAAAAIBAJ&sjid=UwYEAAAAIBAJ&pg=3636,1012288&dq= Student's threat to shoot teacher was dismissed by classmates as joke], ''[[Ocala Star-Banner]]'' (December 18, 1983)</ref>\n|-\n| March 13, 1984\n| [[Castres]], France\n| \n| 2 dead\n|\n| A 15-year-old student killed his teacher, who had sent him to the headmaster for being late, and shot himself in the head. He died on the way to the hospital.<ref>[http://suche.abendblatt.de:8000/article.php?xmlurl=http://87.230.59.37/ha/1984/xml/19840314xml/habxml840103_9060.xml&pdfurl=http://87.230.59.37/ha/1984/pdf/19840314.pdf/ASV_HAB_19840314_HA_032.pdf Lehrer erschossen]{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, ''[[Hamburger Abendblatt]]'' (March 14, 1984)</ref>\n|-\n|March 29, 1985\n|[[Spartanburg, South Carolina|Spartanburg]], [[South Carolina]], United States\n|\n|\n|\n|A 15 year old freshman held four students [[hostage]] at [[Paul M. Dorman High School]], after leaving school grounds when being accused of drinking, and returning to the school with a loaded .38 Colt [[revolver]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.goupstate.com/news/19990502/student-gunman-took-hostages-in-spartanburg-14-years-ago-it-happened-here|title=Student gunman took hostages in Spartanburg 14 years ago It happened here|last=PREVATTE|first=PAM|work=GoUpstate|access-date=2018-02-20|language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n|September 4, 1985\n|[[Richmond, Virginia]], United States\n| Student, 12-years-old\n| 1 dead\n|\n| At the end of the second day of school at East End Middle School, a 12-year-old boy shot a girl with his mother's gun. <ref> https://www.k12academics.com/school-shootings/history-school-shootings-united-states}</ref>\n|-\n| October 18, 1985\n| [[Detroit]], [[Michigan]], United States\n| \n| \n| 6 injured\n| During halftime of the homecoming football game between [[Northwestern High School (Michigan)|Northwestern]] and [[Murray-Wright High School|Murray-Wright]], a boy who had been in a fight earlier that day retaliated with a shotgun, wounding six students.<ref>{{cite news |newspaper=[[Houston Chronicle]] |title=6 Shot, Injured at Homecoming|url=https://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl/1985_45387/6-shot-injured-at-homecoming.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |newspaper=Houston Chronicle |title=Fight Occurred At School Before Shootings|url=https://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl/1985_45930/fight-occurred-at-school-before-shootings.html}}</ref>\n|-\n| November 26, 1985\n| [[Spanaway, Washington]], United States\n| Heather Smith, 14\n| 3 dead\n|\n| At Spanaway Junior High School, a student, 14-year-old Heather Smith = who was apparently distraught over a failed romance and bad grades - fatally shot her her 15-year-old ex-boyfriend, Gordon Pickett, and another youth at the school, before killing herself. The second youth, 14-year-old Christopher Ricco, was shot while trying to prevent Smith from shooting Pickett.<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://apnews.com/075d33aa6600d2e6b30d969ba3edaf0d|title=''Distraught Over Losing Boyfriend, Girl Kills Two, Then Herself''|date=November 27, 1985}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 3, 1985\n| [[Concord, New Hampshire]], United States\n| Louis Cartier, 16\n| 1 dead\n| \n| At [[Concord High School (New Hampshire)|Concord High School]], Louis \"Louie\" Cartier, a 16-year-old male dropout, entered the school with a shotgun and took two students hostage. Responding officers fatally shot him as he aimed at a teacher.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p0qPt8jUr7E&t=9m|title=ABC News Nightline, Jan 29, 1986 \u2013 Challenger disaster one month after fatal school shooting|work=YouTube|accessdate=October 1, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Sarah Chalsma |url=http://www.concordmonitor.com/home/3438627-95/1985-concord-shooting-believe |title=My Turn: In 1985, Concord High was the site of another school shooting |publisher=concordmonitor.com |date=2012-12-19 |accessdate=January 14, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150627164824/http://www.concordmonitor.com/home/3438627-95/1985-concord-shooting-believe |archivedate=June 27, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Tom Mooney |url=http://www.apnewsarchive.com/1985/Wounded-Teen-Dies-Day-After-Police-Shots-Ended-Hostage-Incident/id-af067d94a4e319a31af445ae0190dcff |title=Wounded Teen Dies Day After Police Shots Ended Hostage Incident |agency=Associated Press |date=1985-12-04 |accessdate=January 14, 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 9, 1985\n| [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]], United States\n| Male mental health patient, 22\n| \n|\n| At Archbishop Ryan High School for Boys, a 22-year-old mental health patient took 6 students at the school hostage, with what ended up being a starter pistol. No one was hurt in the ordeal. <ref>https://www.k12academics.com/school-shootings/history-school-shootings-united-states </ref>\n|-\n| December 10, 1985\n| [[Portland, Connecticut]], United States\n| Floyd Warmsley, 13\n| 1 dead\n| 2 injured\n| 13-year-old student Floyd Warmsley fatally shot a school custodian, wounded both the principal and school secretary, and held a student hostage with an assault pistol at Portland Junior High School in [[Portland, Connecticut]] - after he had been suspended for a minor issue. His aunt convinced him to surrender.<ref name=\"atlanta121185\">{{cite news|title=Junior-high student, 13, arrested after shooting death at school|date=1985-12-11|url =http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=AT&p_theme=at&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EB7C1D85565E733&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM|work=[[The Atlanta Journal-Constitution]]|accessdate = 2009-04-18}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 6, 1986\n| [[Dolton, Illinois]], United States\n| ..., 14\n|\n| 1 injured\n| A 14-year-old student shot and wounded his math teacher at [[Thornridge High School]].<ref>[https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/chicagotribune/access/24994037.html?dids=24994037:24994037&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&date=Mar+07%2C+1986&author=Andrew+Bagnato+and+Andrew+Fegelman&pub=Chicago+Tribune+(pre-1997+Fulltext)&desc=SUBURB+TEEN+SHOOTS+TEACHER+AT+SCHOOL&pqatl=google Suburb teen shoots teacher at school], ''[[Chicago Tribune]]'' (March 7, 1986)</ref><ref>[http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=CSTB&p_theme=cstb&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EB36CF4D1CAABF7&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM Dolton cops hold gun-wielding boy], ''[[Chicago Sun-Times]]'' (March 7, 1986)</ref>\n|-\n| October 8, 1986\n| [[Dallas, Texas]], United States\n| Kenneth Lee Jackson, 19\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 16-year-old Cody Cobbins was shot and killed on a school bus by the older brother of a 17-year-old boy he was arguing with over a seat. The shooter was later sentenced to 40 years in prison on March 5, 1987.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.co