-of-appeals-unpublished/294823.pdf?ts=1337947679|publisher=State of Michigan|date=May 24, 2012|accessdate = September 5, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 31, 2008\n| [[Stockton Springs]],<br>[[Maine]],<br>United States\n| Randall Hofland, 55\n|\n|\n| Eleven fifth-grade students were taken hostage in a classroom at Stockton Springs Elementary School, in [[Stockton Springs]], [[Maine]]. The hostage situation ended within 30 minutes when the gunman surrendered to a [[state trooper]]. The hostage taker, 55-year-old Randall Hofland, was wanted by authorities for pointing a handgun at an officer during a traffic stop and then fleeing.<ref name=\"maine1031\">{{cite news|title=Maine Gunman Held Fifth-Graders Hostage|date=2008-10-31|publisher=CBS News|url =https://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2008/10/31/national/main4560826.shtml?source=RSSattr=U.S._4560826|accessdate = 2009-06-09}}</ref><ref name=\"portland1031\">{{cite news|title=Police ID Alleged School Hostage Taker|date=2008-10-31|publisher=WMTW|url =http://www.wmtw.com/news/17856353/detail.html|accessdate = 2009-06-09}}</ref>\n|-\n| November 12, 2008\n| [[Fort Lauderdale]],<br>[[Florida]],<br>United States\n| Teah Wimberly, 15\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 15-year-old student Amanda Collette was shot to death by her 15-year-old classmate, Teah Wimberly, in a hallway of [[Dillard High School]], in [[Fort Lauderdale]], [[Florida]].<ref name=\"courant118\">{{cite news|first=Joel|last=Marino|title=Wimberly wanted friend to feel her pain, attorney|date=2008-11-18|url =http://www.courant.com/features/columnists/sfl-flbwimberly1118sbnov18,0,452254.story|work=[[The Hartford Courant]]|accessdate = 2009-05-16}}</ref> The shooter was arraigned on the charge of [[first-degree murder]] She was sentenced to 25 years to life in prison.<ref name=\"bsun114\">{{cite news|first=Kathy|last=Bushouse|author2=Tonya Alanez|author3=Mike Clary|title=Student may have told Dillard High officials about gun|date=2008-11-14|url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/topic/sfl-flbdill