on Post]] |date=July 16, 2012 |accessdate=July 16, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 30, 2010\n| [[Oshawa]],<br>[[Ontario]]<br>Canada\n| Jacques Amakon, 18\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Michael McDonald, a 16-year-old student at [[Monsignor Paul Dwyer Catholic High School]], was stabbed to death at a bus stop across from the school. Jacques Amakon, an 18-year-old student, was arrested after the stabbing and charged with [[second-degree murder]]. It was reported that the two students were involved in a dispute.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/article/787988--teens-watch-as-schoolmate-stabbed-to-death-in-oshawa |title=Teens watch as schoolmate stabbed to death in Oshawa |publisher=Thestar.com |date= March 31, 2010|accessdate=2011-03-12 |location=Toronto |first1=Tamara |last1=Baluja |first2=Carola |last2=Vyhnak}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.citytv.com/toronto/citynews/news/local/article/73412--teen-dies-after-stabbing-near-oshawa-school |title=Teen Dies After Stabbing Near Oshawa School |publisher=Citytv.com |date=2010-03-30 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629145700/http://www.citytv.com/toronto/citynews/news/local/article/73412--teen-dies-after-stabbing-near-oshawa-school |archivedate=2011-06-29 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/toronto/student-charged-with-murder-in-teens-stabbing-death/article1518884/ |title=Student charged with murder in teen\u2019s stabbing death |publisher=Theglobeandmail.com |accessdate=2011-03-12 |location=Toronto}}</ref> In July 2012, Amakon was convicted of a lesser charge of manslaughter and was sentenced to 6 years of prison.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.durhamregion.com/news-story/3505940-amakon-gets-six-years-for-killing-of-biggie-mcdonald-in-oshawa/ |title=Amakon gets six years for killing of \"Biggie\" McDonald in Oshawa |publisher=[[Durham Region]] |accessdate=September 1, 2013 |location=}}</ref> \n|-\n| April 28, 2010\n| [[Portsmout