s-title=40th Japan Academy Prize|publisher=Official Japan Academy Prize|language=ja|date=March 3, 2017|accessdate=March 22, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 31st [[Japan Gold Disc Award]]\n| Soundtrack Album of the Year\n| {{won}}<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.golddisc.jp/award/31/Prize_2.html#gd31_16|title=\u7b2c31\u56de\u65e5\u672c\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u30c9\u30c7\u30a3\u30b9\u30af\u5927\u8cde|trans-title=31st Japan Gold Disk Awards|publisher=Official Japan Gold Disc Award|language=ja|accessdate=March 22, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 6th [[Newtype#Newtype Anime Awards|Newtype Anime Awards]]\n| Best Soundtrack\n| {{draw|Runner-up}}<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-10-09/shinkai-your-name-kabaneri-win-top-newtype-anime-awards/.107437|title=Shinkai's 'Your Name.,' 'Kabaneri' Win Top Newtype Anime Awards|work=Anime News Network|date=October 9, 2016|accessdate=March 22, 2019|last=Loo|first=Egan}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Your Name (novel)|''Your Name'' (novel)]], a novelization of the film\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{AllMusic|id=your-name-original-motion-picture-soundtrack-mw0002998169|title=''Your Name.''}}\n* {{MusicBrainz release group|mbid=f2c10017-ead9-47a4-8ef1-928cff3ac1ec|name=Your Name.|type=album}}\n\n{{Radwimps}}\n\n[[Category:2016 soundtracks]]\n[[Category:Film soundtracks]]\n[[Category:Radwimps albums]]\n[[Category:Anime soundtracks]]\n[[Category:Universal Music Japan albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Your Name\n| type       = soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Radwimps]]\n| cover      = Radwimps Your Name Album Cover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = August 24, 2016\n| recorded   = 2016\n| language   = {{hlist|Japanese|English}}\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Rock music|Rock]]\n| length     = 72:05\n| label      = {{hlist|[[EMI Records|EMI]]|[[Universal Music Japan|Universal Japan]]}}\n| producer   = [[Radwimps]]\n| chronology = [[Radwimps]] albums\n| prev_title = [[Batsu to Maru to Tsumi to]]\n| prev_year  = 2013\n| next_title = [[Human Bloom (album)|Human Bloom]]\n| next_year  = 2016\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Your Name\n | type        = soundtrack\n | single1     = [[Zenzenzense]]\n | single1date = July 25, 2016\n}}\n}}\n{{nihongo|'''''Your Name.'''''|\u541b\u306e\u540d\u306f\u3002|Kimi no Na wa.|lead=yes}} is the eighth studio album by Japanese rock band [[Radwimps]] and the soundtrack for the 2016 Japanese animated film ''[[Your Name]]'', released on August 24, 2016, by [[Universal Music Japan]]. It debuted at #1 on [[Oricon]]'s weekly album rankings on September 5, 2016, with 58,000 copies sold.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2077563/full/|title=\u3010\u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u3011RADWIMPS\u3001\u521d\u306e\u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e0\u9996\u4f4d \u30a2\u30cb\u30e1\u6620\u753b\u300e\u541b\u306e\u540d\u306f\u3002\u300f\u30b5\u30f3\u30c8\u30e9|publisher=[[Oricon]]|date=August 30, 2016|accessdate=September 10, 2016|language=ja|trans-title=RADWIMPS' soundtrack album for the anime movie 'Your Name.' debuted at number one}}</ref> It received a [[List of music recording certifications#Albums|digital download album certification]] of Gold from the [[Recording Industry Association of Japan]] for sales of 100,000.<ref name=\"DL Cert\">{{cite web |url= https://aramajapan.com/chart/the-recording-industry-association-of-japan-releases-its-digital-certifications-for-november-list-of-2016s-certified-releases/68348/|title= The Recording Industry Association of Japan Releases Its Digital Certifications for November + List of 2016\u2019s Certified Releases|accessdate= December 20, 2016|work= Arama! Japan|author=Ronald}}</ref> The album also charted on [[Billboard charts|US ''Billboard'']]. It peaked at #16 on [[Top Heatseekers|''Billboard'' Heatseekers Albums]],<ref name=\"Heat\">{{cite web|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/heatseekers-albums/2017-04-29|title=Heatseekers Albums {{!}} Charts|date=April 29, 2017|accessdate=March 22, 2019}}</ref> #15 on ''Billboard'' Soundtracks Albums,<ref name=\"Soundtr\">{{cite web|website=Billboard|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/soundtracks/2017-04-29|title=Soundtracks Albums {{!}} Charts|date=April 29, 2017|accessdate=March 22, 2019}}</ref> and #2 on ''Billboard'' World Albums chart.<ref name=\"World\">{{cite web|website=Billboard|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/world-albums/2017-04-29|title=World Albums {{!}} Charts|date=April 29, 2017|accessdate=March 22, 2019}}</ref> The vocal tracks were re-recorded in English and became available digitally on January 27, 2017, with a CD release date of March 10, 2017.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-02-15/radwimps-new-video-previews-your-name-film-english-songs/.112263|title=Radwimps' New Video Previews 'Your Name.' Film's English Songs|work=[[Anime News Network]]|last=Sherman|first=Jennifer|date=February 15, 2017|accessdate=March 7, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nAccording to vocalist Yojiro Noda, it took almost a year and a half to make the whole entire score for ''Your Name'' movie.<ref name=\"Forbes\">{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/olliebarder/2017/04/18/radwimps-on-how-they-scored-the_music-for-the-anime-blockbuster-your-name/|title=Radwimps on How They Scored the Music for the Anime Blockbuster 'Your Name'|magazine=[[Forbes]]|last=Barder|first=Ollie|date=April 18, 2017|accessdate=March 24, 2019}}</ref> Director [[Makoto Shinkai]], who is also a fan of the band, approached Noda through producer Genki Kawamura as soon as the production of movie was confirmed.<ref name=\"Japan Times\">{{cite news|url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/culture/2017/03/16/music/radwimps-ride-name-train-fame/|title=Radwimps were the perfect choice when it came to soundtracking 'Your Name.'|newspaper=[[The Japan Times]]|last=Michel|first=Patrick St.|date=March 16, 2017|accessdate=March 24, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Time Out\">{{cite news|url=https://www.timeout.com/bangkok/music/q-a-with-radwimps|title=Q&A with Radwimps|magazine=[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out]]|last=Rodsom|first=Sopida|date=December 22, 2016|accessdate=March 24, 2019}}</ref> When recording the soundtrack, the band was not able to see the actual animation until it was all finished, so they wrote music based on the script and words of the director, which caused many compositions to be adjusted to fit the animation. \"It was really difficult to arrange music to fit the animation by the second,\" said guitarist Akira Kuwahara. \"The songwriting process was moving forward at the same time with the animation so it influenced each other. The music changed the story, the lines, and if the new scene was created, we changed the music. It was a creative process,\" added Noda.<ref name=\"Forbes\"/><ref name=\"PopCrush\">{{cite news|url=https://popcrush.com/radwimps-j-rock-your-name-human-bloom-interview/|title=J-rock band Radwimps talk making music for critically acclaimed 'Your Name' : Interview|website=[[PopCrush]]|last=Russell|first=Erica|date=April 11, 2017|accessdate=March 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n| id = \n| collapsed = \n| headline = \n| extra_column = \n| total_length = 1:12:05\n\n| 1 = \n| all_writing = \n| all_lyrics = \n| all_music = \n| all_arrangements = \nYojiro Noda\n| 2 =\n\n| writing_credits =\n\n| title1 = Yume T\u014dr\u014d (\u5922\u706f\u7c60, \"Dream Lantern<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/your-name/1174228968|title=''Your Name.'' by RADWIMPS|website=[[iTunes]]|date=August 24, 2016|accessdate=September 10, 2016}}</ref>\")\n| length1 = 2:09\n| music1 = Noda\n| lyrics1 = Yojiro Noda\n\n| title2 = Mitsuha no Ts\u016bgaku (\u4e09\u8449\u306e\u901a\u5b66, \"School Road\")\n| length2 = 1:07\n| music2 = Yojiro Noda\n\n| title3 = Itomori K\u014dk\u014d (\u7cf8\u5b88\u9ad8\u6821, \"Itomori High School\")\n| length3 = 1:48\n| music3 = Yojiro Noda\n\n| title4 = Hajimete no T\u0